-- Car Bomb Explodes in Northern Ireland, Damaging Shopping Mall; No Injuries
-- B y   C o l m   H e a t l e y
-- 2010-10-05T00:55:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-05/car-bomb-explodes-in-northern-ireland-damaging-shopping-mall-no-injuries.html
Northern Ireland police said a car
bomb exploded close to a bank in Londonderry, in the north-west
of the U.K. region, causing “substantial damage” to a retail
complex. No injuries were reported.  A warning had been received and the bomb was detonated in a
car shortly after midnight local time, police said in a recorded
message. The area is being evacuated, police said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
